{"title":"Dinolfo Cycles weld up a classic steel hardtail with all the standards","link":"https://bikerumor.com/dinolfo-cycles-weld-up-a-classic-steel-hardtail-with-all-the-standards/","date":1639756128000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095814/dinolfo-cycles-hardtail-mountain-bike.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"458\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095814/dinolfo-cycles-hardtail-mountain-bike-800x458.jpg\" alt=\"dinolfo cycles steel hardtail mtb\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095814/dinolfo-cycles-hardtail-mountain-bike-800x458.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095814/dinolfo-cycles-hardtail-mountain-bike-297x170.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095814/dinolfo-cycles-hardtail-mountain-bike-120x69.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095814/dinolfo-cycles-hardtail-mountain-bike-768x439.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095814/dinolfo-cycles-hardtail-mountain-bike-1536x878.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095814/dinolfo-cycles-hardtail-mountain-bike.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-280974\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Dinolfo Cycles has just released their first hardtail mountain bike. Like their gravel frame, the Dinolfo Hardtail is hand-fabricated from custom-butted 4130 steel tubing at their HQ in Wiesbaden, Germany. The brand decided to keep things classic and simple, opting to run all the common standards allowing the bike’s unique geometry to do all the talking.</p><h2>Dinolfo Hardtail Mountain Bike</h2><div id=\"attachment_281128\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095938/dinolfo-hardtail-mtb-steel-frame.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-281128\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095938/dinolfo-hardtail-mtb-steel-frame.jpg\" alt=\"dinolfo hardtail mtb 140mm fork\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1024\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095938/dinolfo-hardtail-mtb-steel-frame.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095938/dinolfo-hardtail-mtb-steel-frame-297x190.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095938/dinolfo-hardtail-mtb-steel-frame-800x512.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095938/dinolfo-hardtail-mtb-steel-frame-120x77.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095938/dinolfo-hardtail-mtb-steel-frame-768x492.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095938/dinolfo-hardtail-mtb-steel-frame-1536x983.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-281128\">The Dinolfo Hardtail large frame weighs a claimed 2.1 kg; the maximum rider weight is 100 kg</p></div><p>There’s very little <em>to know</em> about the Dinolfo Hardtail, and that’s just how the brand wanted it; fast, functional and fuss-free. The frameset sees all the regular mountain bike standards, if such a thing exists; boost 148mm rear end spacing, a 44mm headtube, 180mm post mount brake and a 73mm threaded BSA bottom bracket.</p><div id=\"attachment_281130\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17102052/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-mtb-intend-inverted-fork-140mm-travel.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-281130\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17102052/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-mtb-intend-inverted-fork-140mm-travel.jpg\" alt=\"dinolfo steel hardtail mountain bike inverted intend fork 140mm travel\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1400\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17102052/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-mtb-intend-inverted-fork-140mm-travel.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17102052/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-mtb-intend-inverted-fork-140mm-travel-297x260.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17102052/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-mtb-intend-inverted-fork-140mm-travel-800x700.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17102052/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-mtb-intend-inverted-fork-140mm-travel-120x105.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17102052/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-mtb-intend-inverted-fork-140mm-travel-768x672.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17102052/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-mtb-intend-inverted-fork-140mm-travel-1536x1344.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-281130\">The Dinolfo frame gets four bottle cage/accessory mounting points; two on the top of the downtube and two on the underside of top tube</p></div><p>The Dinolfo’s geometry is optimised around 29″ wheels and a 612mm axle-to-crown fork, or 140mm travel; the one picture here is a custom-made 140mm travel inverted fork from Intend. They do tell us the frame geometry can also work well with fork travel anywhere between 130mm and 150mm, however.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095819/dinolfo-hardtail-geometry.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095819/dinolfo-hardtail-geometry.jpg\" alt=\"dinolfo hardtail steel mtb geometry chart size large\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1130\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095819/dinolfo-hardtail-geometry.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095819/dinolfo-hardtail-geometry-297x210.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095819/dinolfo-hardtail-geometry-800x565.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095819/dinolfo-hardtail-geometry-120x85.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095819/dinolfo-hardtail-geometry-768x542.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095819/dinolfo-hardtail-geometry-1536x1085.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>A 447mm rear-center length on the large frame gives the Dinolfo clearance for a 29″ x 2.5″ wide tire out back. Almost equally balanced front-to-rear, reach comes in a tad longer at 450mm. The head angle sits at 65° paired with a 74° seat tube angle. Though they make not look too dissimilar, the Dinolfo’s geometry is a little more conservative as compared to that of the mixed-wheel <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/starling-roost-mullet-hardtail-mountain-bike-is-a-140mm-stainless-steel-stunner/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Starling Roost Hardtail</a> we wrote about earlier this week.</p><div id=\"attachment_281127\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095838/dinolfo-hardtail-tire-clearance.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-281127\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095838/dinolfo-hardtail-tire-clearance.jpg\" alt=\"dinolfo hardtail tire clearance\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1225\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095838/dinolfo-hardtail-tire-clearance.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095838/dinolfo-hardtail-tire-clearance-297x227.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095838/dinolfo-hardtail-tire-clearance-800x613.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095838/dinolfo-hardtail-tire-clearance-120x92.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095838/dinolfo-hardtail-tire-clearance-768x588.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17095838/dinolfo-hardtail-tire-clearance-1536x1176.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-281127\">Tire clearance on the medium frame is a little less; 29″ x 2.4″</p></div><div id=\"attachment_281132\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17103949/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-frame-details.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-281132\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17103949/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-frame-details.jpg\" alt=\"dinolfo hardtail mtb frame details steel tubing\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1257\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17103949/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-frame-details.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17103949/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-frame-details-297x233.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17103949/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-frame-details-800x629.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17103949/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-frame-details-120x94.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17103949/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-frame-details-768x603.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/12/17103949/dinolfo-hardtail-steel-frame-details-1536x1207.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-281132\">Other frame details: 32T maximum chainring size; frame runs a 30.9mm seat post with a 35mm clamp</p></div><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p>The Dinolfo Hardtail is sold as a frame only, available now direct from Dinolfo for 2590.00 € including VAT and shipping. Lead time on a frame is currently 5 weeks. Dinolfo currently only ship within Germany but will expand to other European countries mid 2022.</p><p><a href=\"https://dinolfo-cycles.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Dinolfo-Cycles.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"f638b2afd9624955c4f8bdd159cb07af741b7e194653689ed07954b64c6d500f","category":"Cycling"}